name: 4-Ingredient Keto Peanut Butter Cookies
author: Fioa
summary: Kids will love these scrumptious low-carb keto cookies; all you need is peanut butter, vanilla extract, an egg, and some sugar substitute.
ingredients: ½ cup low-calorie natural sweetener (such as Swerve®)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Combine peanut butter, sweetener, egg, and vanilla extract in a bowl; mix well until a dough is formed
Place on the prepared baking sheet and press down twice with a fork in a criss-cross pattern
Bake in the the preheated oven until edges are golden, 12 to 15 minutes
Cool on the baking sheet for 1 minute before removing to a wire rack to cool completely
